<div id="review_2029755989" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2029755989" />
    <a title="Jennifer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/39942856-jennifer"><img alt="Jennifer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1518926670p2/39942856.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2029755989?book_show_action=true">Jul 29, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jennifer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jennifer" href="/user/show/39942856-jennifer">Jennifer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39942856-jennifer?shelf=adult">adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39942856-jennifer?shelf=christian-fiction">christian-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39942856-jennifer?shelf=takes-their-time">takes-their-time</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39942856-jennifer?shelf=part-of-a-series">part-of-a-series</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39942856-jennifer?shelf=borrowed-library">borrowed-library</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39942856-jennifer?shelf=not-a-mh">not-a-mh</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39942856-jennifer?shelf=clean">clean</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39942856-jennifer?shelf=all-the-lies-or-secrets">all-the-lies-or-secrets</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39942856-jennifer?shelf=sad">sad</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39942856-jennifer?shelf=stars-2-5">stars-2-5</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2029755989" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4794992130368628938">2.5 stars.<br/><br/>This was an encouraging story of how God can redeem any situation. I enjoyed the dual povs, the full scope of the story, the utter lack of ow/om drama, and the slow burn romance. I appreciated how clean it was and how uplifting the story was. I also enjoyed the historical aspect of this story. The society in the South post-Civil War, the differing attitudes toward freedmen, and the stud farm atmosphere were compelling and engaging to read. <br/><br/><b> And yet </b> I didn&apos;t find that I enjoyed this ov</span>
  <span id="freeText4794992130368628938" style="display:none">2.5 stars.<br /><br />This was an encouraging story of how God can redeem any situation. I enjoyed the dual povs, the full scope of the story, the utter lack of ow/om drama, and the slow burn romance. I appreciated how clean it was and how uplifting the story was. I also enjoyed the historical aspect of this story. The society in the South post-Civil War, the differing attitudes toward freedmen, and the stud farm atmosphere were compelling and engaging to read. <br /><br /><b> And yet </b> I didn't find that I enjoyed this overly much because the telling of this story was slow. And the book was long. Over four hundred pages. Which didn't seem completely necessary to me. I understand that the author was trying to tell a convincing tale of two people overcoming their pasts and that does realistically take time, but parts of this story dragged. It really felt like the author could have accomplished her goal and still have edited out at least seventy-five pages.<br /><br />Part of the slowness was due to the fact that so much time was spent on how weak the h felt. I don't need to read about a perfect character. Far from it. I do however need to feel not annoyed all the time at how the h cowers around horses or how she can't find it in herself to speak her mind. I couldn't help but feel frustrated by her for at least the first two hundred pages. And it seemed like many of the other pages of this book were dedicated to showing how much guilt the H felt about perpetuating his deception. I understand the premise of his lies of omission, but didn't like how long it took him to come clean.<br /><br />Overall, this was a well-researched, full developed story about the struggles of two very realistic individuals. I would recommend this to anyone who enjoys Reconstruction period historical romance. </span>
  <a data-text-id="4794992130368628938" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


