<div id="review_3987530886" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3987530886" />
    <a title="Clarissa Choo" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/117417791-clarissa-choo"><img alt="Clarissa Choo" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607589783p2/117417791.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3987530886?book_show_action=true">May 06, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Clarissa Choo" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Clarissa Choo" href="/user/show/117417791-clarissa-choo">Clarissa Choo</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3987530886" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6640677845356368056">I read this some months ago, so my review is based on what I remember.<br/><br/>This intricate tale has a beautiful writing style which I very much enjoy (although the description can get a tad too fancy for me as they distract me from the plot sometimes). Overall, the characters and Biblical messages are encouraging.<br/><br/>However, the Biblical themes, specifically from Cooper’s side begin as the main dish of his story but its significance appears to have downgraded to a side because of the romance plot. Althou</span>
  <span id="freeText6640677845356368056" style="display:none">I read this some months ago, so my review is based on what I remember.<br /><br />This intricate tale has a beautiful writing style which I very much enjoy (although the description can get a tad too fancy for me as they distract me from the plot sometimes). Overall, the characters and Biblical messages are encouraging.<br /><br />However, the Biblical themes, specifically from Cooper’s side begin as the main dish of his story but its significance appears to have downgraded to a side because of the romance plot. Although Cooper’s arc for that theme is resolved somewhere in the middle, I am disappointed that it is diminished to the point where I wonder about the purpose of incorporating it.<br /><br />As for the pace and plot, it feels as though the author is building a lot of good plot tension and complexity only to slice it quickly, giving me a sense of incompleteness. And if my memory does not fail me, I think some subplots are left untied.<br /><br />I probably shouldn’t have high expectations upon reading because this book has disappointed me.<br /><br />The spoilers below give readers a heads up on certain romantic scenes and character thoughts I dislike. I’m surprised no reviewer here has mentioned these from what I've searched so far.<br /><br />Spoilers<br /><a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[- Two kissing scenes are quite long and detailed, and they appear to give off a bit of sexual tension in my perspective (e.g. Cooper feels the curve of her back). I’m not sure if I should label them as make-out scenes, but it depends on how the reader defines a make-out scene. If you’re sensitive to kissing scenes, this spoiler is to give you a heads up so you won’t get caught off guard and are prepared to skip them.<br /><br />- Although it’s vague, he has repeated thoughts of her figure. Once, he vaguely imagines her womanly form next to him in bed.  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span></span>
  <a data-text-id="6640677845356368056" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


